---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About | Paddle Today"
  description="How Paddle Today scores rivers, handles confidence, and why coverage starts with rivers that have the strongest live data."
>
  <section class="info-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">About Paddle Today</p>
    <h1>River calls built around usefulness, not volume.</h1>
    <p class="muted">
      Paddle Today is a work in progress built around one question: is this river worth paddling today? The goal is to turn messy live data into a clear, explainable call you can act on.
    </p>
    <div class="info-hero__actions">
      <a class="river-link river-link--inline" href="/request-river/">Request a river</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="info-grid" aria-label="How Paddle Today works">
    <article class="info-card">
      <p class="eyebrow">Method</p>
      <h2>How the call is made</h2>
      <p class="muted">
        Each river call combines current gauge value, recent trend, weather risk, seasonality, and river-specific threshold notes. The result is a score, a confidence level, and a short explanation in plain language.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="info-card">
      <p class="eyebrow">Confidence</p>
      <h2>Why some rivers score better than others</h2>
      <p class="muted">
        Confidence depends on the freshness and quality of the inputs. Direct gauges, stronger published ranges, and current weather reads lead to stronger calls. Stale or thin evidence lowers confidence.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="info-card">
      <p class="eyebrow">Coverage</p>
      <h2>Why coverage starts small</h2>
      <p class="muted">
        We start with rivers that have direct gauges and enough usable guidance to score them without guessing too much. Coverage grows as the evidence gets better. The goal is better calls, not bigger lists.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="info-panel">
    <p class="eyebrow">Ground rules</p>
    <h2>Always verify before you launch.</h2>
    <p class="muted">
      River levels, weather, access, and hazards can change quickly. Paddle Today is a planning tool, not a substitute for local judgment, source verification, or on-the-ground scouting.
    </p>
    <ul class="compact-list">
      <li>Check the original gauge and source links on the river page.</li>
      <li>Recheck weather, wind, and storms before you drive.</li>
      <li>Confirm put-in, take-out, parking, and land-access rules locally.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
